reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best tampons for my teen
reviews.reviewText: When my daughter decided she wanted to try using tampons, I wanted her to use an organic, non-toxic version. I know as a teen I sometimes had a hard time with applicators so she tried these and is very happy with them. I feel good knowing they’re not harming her young body, plus they’re super discreet and easy to carry in a pocket. I use a menstrual cup but when I need a tampon, this is my go-to brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Make the healthy switch to organic cotton tampons!
reviews.reviewText: Every woman should know about organic tampons! Conventional tampon brands like Tampax or Kotex (same company!) are made with GMO cotton which is sprayed with birth-defect and cancer causing chemicals made by Monsanto. No woman wants to put that in her body. Major brand tampons are then chemically treated and bleached. Cotton is absorbent, which is why we use it for this purpose. Cotton will absorb all of those horrible chemicals and then they will leach into your soft woman tissues. Make the switch! It's not more expensive to use organic cotton tampons! I have heard from multiple women who have switched that their cramps were way less intense. Natracare brand also makes tampons with an applicator for those who prefer it. Smart packaging and friendlier for the Earth with less plastic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good products, good delivery.
reviews.reviewText: Order was made via OxKom on Amazon Marketplace. The products arrived very well packaged, as advertised, and on the day they said they would.As for the tampons themselves, Natracare is my new go-to brand for pads and tampons because they "use certified organic 100% cotton and sustainably-sourced natural, plant based materials" and they do the job. My only caution to a first time user of this brand would be that the tampons absorb less than you might think. However, since one should change their tampons often anyway, it is actually for the best. The pads on the other hand, I find the regular ones way more absorbent than they should be based on their appearance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2018
reviews.reviewText: This size is great. I thought it would be too big and I ordered by mistake. However, decided to try and they fit me just fine. Worked great and discovered that I didn't have to change them throughout the day/night as many times as I do the next smaller size. Less work for me and I'm using less product, which means spending less money. Absorbs a lot of blood, goes in and out flawlessly. I've been using these (and this brand) for years and I'm very satisfied.
